I. Fret

Well, tere are also two types of Cord Shapes and they will help to find All the
Minor and Major Chords also the # and b Chords.

B-minor as example:

|-------|-(|)--|-------|-------|------|------|
|-------|-(|)--|--( )--|-------|------|------|
|-------|-(|)--|-------|--( )--|------|------|
|-------|-(|)--|-------|--( )--|------|------|
|-------|-(X)--|-------|-------|------|------|
|-------|-(|)--|-------|-------|------|------|
I. Fret

D-minor:

|-------|-(|)--|-------|-------|------|------|
|-------|-(|)--|--( )--|-------|------|------|
|-------|-(|)--|-------|--( )--|------|------|
|-------|-(|)--|-------|--( )--|------|------|
|-------|-(X)--|-------|-------|------|------|
|-------|-(|)--|-------|-------|------|------|
IV. Fret

The Chord shape was moved up or down the Neck. The X indicates the Root Note. If you
wand to find the A#-minor Chord, locate the A# on the A-String (First Fret) and take 
the minor shape (Shown above)

F-Major as Example:

|-(|)--|-------|-------|------|------|-------|
|-(|)--|-------|-------|------|------|-------|
|-(|)--|--( )--|-------|------|------|-------|
|-(|)--|-------|--( )--|------|------|-------|
|-(|)--|-------|--( )--|------|------|-------|
|-(X)--|-------|-------|------|------|-------|
I. Fret

G-Major as Example:

|-(|)--|-------|-------|------|------|-------|
|-(|)--|-------|-------|------|------|-------|
|-(|)--|--( )--|-------|------|------|-------|
|-(|)--|-------|--( )--|------|------|-------|
|-(|)--|-------|--( )--|------|------|-------|
|-(X)--|-------|-------|------|------|-------|
III. Fret

The Major Chord shape was Just moved to the Root Note. (Indicated by an X)
Same process as minor Chords !

After a while of Playing you will find the Chords automatically. Play Them every
Day to keep them in Memory. 

Bye.....

